# ☪️ Halal Checker — Deployment Guide

AI-powered halal ingredient checker. Free to use globally.

## Project Structure

```
halal-checker/
├── api/
│   └── check.js        ← Serverless function (Anthropic API proxy)
├── public/
│   └── index.html      ← Frontend app
├── vercel.json         ← Vercel routing config
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

---

## 🚀 Deploy to Vercel (Step-by-Step)

### Step 1 — Create GitHub Repository

1. Go to https://github.com and sign in (or create free account)
2. Click **New repository**
3. Name it: `halal-checker`
4. Set to **Public**
5. Click **Create repository**
6. Upload all files from this folder (drag & drop into GitHub UI)

### Step 2 — Deploy on Vercel

1. Go to https://vercel.com and sign in with your GitHub account
2. Click **Add New Project**
3. Select your `halal-checker` repository
4. Click **Deploy** (Vercel auto-detects the config)

### Step 3 — Add Anthropic API Key (CRITICAL)

1. In Vercel dashboard → your project → **Settings** → **Environment Variables**
2. Add:
   - **Name:** `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
   - **Value:** your key from https://console.anthropic.com
3. Click **Save**
4. Go to **Deployments** → click **Redeploy** (to apply the env variable)

### Step 4 — Add Custom Domain (Optional)

1. Buy domain e.g. `halalcheck.app` at Namecheap (~$10/yr)
2. In Vercel → **Settings** → **Domains** → add your domain
3. Follow DNS instructions (point nameservers to Vercel)
4. Done — live globally in ~10 minutes

